Bug Hunter: You are reviewing a `Spring Boot` service responsible for inventory updates. Users report that when an error occurs during the stock deduction, the transaction is not rolling back, leading to data inconsistency. You find the following snippet:

java
@Service
public class InventoryService {

    public void updateInventory(Long id, int quantity) {
        // Business logic
        processUpdate(id, quantity);
    }

    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void processUpdate(Long id, int quantity) {
        // Database operations
        if (quantity < 0) throw new RuntimeException("Invalid quantity");
    }
}
